{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"80a9782a-5cc2-4597-a5bb-71adc1ddf545","agentId":"a1fbe1fe173d5f602","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Create the test list for Conway's Game of Life kata.\n\n## Specification\n\nImplement Conway's Game of Life with an infinite grid (sparse representation, only track living cells).\n\n### Rules:\n1. **Underpopulation**: Any live cell with fewer than 2 live neighbors dies\n2. **Survival**: Any live cell with 2 or 3 live neighbors lives on\n3. **Overpopulation**: Any live cell with more than 3 live neighbors dies\n4. **Reproduction**: Any dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive\n\n### Constraints:\n- Grid is infinite in all directions (positive and negative x/y)\n- Only track living cells (sparse representation)\n- Cells are identified by coordinates (x, y)\n- A \"generation\" transforms the current state to the next state\n- The implementation should accept an arbitrary grid of living cells and output the next generation\n\n### Examples from the spec:\n\n**Underpopulation**: [(0,1), (1,1)] → [] (each has 1 neighbor)\n**Survival**: center cell (1,1) with 3 neighbors survives\n**Overpopulation**: center cell (1,1) with 4+ neighbors dies\n**Reproduction**: dead cell (1,1) with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive\n**Single cell dies**: [(0,0)] → []\n**Block (still life)**: [(0,0), (1,0), (0,1), (1,1)] → same\n**Blinker (oscillator)**: [(0,0), (0,1), (0,2)] → [(-1,1), (0,1), (1,1)]\n\n## Output files\n- Test file: `src/game-of-life.spec.ts`\n- Implementation file: `src/game-of-life.ts`\n\n## Technical setup\n- TypeScript with Vitest\n- Use `describe`, `it`, `expect` from Vitest\n- Use `.spec.ts` extension\n- Local imports use explicit `.js` extensions\n- Run tests with `pnpm test`\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously."},"uuid":"cb1cb394-b5d7-4f7f-992b-8a90cfe81ecd","timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:18:54.961Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-0